
This example is for basic curd operation using Panache with h2 in-memory

To Access
- Quarkus DevUI : http://localhost:8080/q/dev-ui/
- To see the Swagger Open API Docs : http://localhost:8080/q/swagger-ui/


To Add User :

curl -X 'POST' \
  'http://localhost:8080/users' \
  -H 'accept: text/plain' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"firstName": "Dean","lastName": "Ambrose"}'

--------------------------------------------------------
Get all Users :

curl -X 'GET' \
  'http://localhost:8080/users' \
  -H 'accept: application/json'

----------------------------------------------------------
Get User By Id

curl -X 'GET' \
  'http://localhost:8080/users/1' \
  -H 'accept: application/json'

----------------------------------------------------------

